Transfer guru, Fabrizio Romano, has revealed that Chelsea plans to unveil Mykhaylo Mudryk as a new signing today. Romano made this known in a tweet via his Twitter handle on Sunday afternoon. He tweeted, “Chelsea plan confirmed: they want to unveil Mykhaylo Mudryk as new signing today at Stamford Bridge. “Understand that some of the add-ons in €100m package deal are related to Chelsea to win Premier League or the Champions League during 7 years of contract.” Mudryk, who is currently in London, is joining Chelsea from Shakhtar Donetsk. The Ukrainian was widely expected to join Chelsea’s London rivals, Arsenal, but the negotiations have been lingering for over two weeks.